ory of shaking at the station red triangle another focus of the research group is the development of numerical methods for computing the growth of ruptures from nucleation regions at the scale of a few meters to fully developed earthquakes that propagate tens or hundred of kilometers all without making compromises in parameter values constrained by laboratory studies related categories natural hazards keywords earthquakes and volcanoes related departments school of earth sciences geophysics view all featured stories department of geophysics 397 panama mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints related resources hartley conference center health and safety computers resources room resources how can we help maps & directions stanfordwho office of the registrar contact us connect to earth sciences facebook itunes u twitter youtube
